CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper January 14, 1956, pg. B24, reads: "Schenley's Choir Sings - The fine a cappella choir of Schenley High School was extended an invitation to participate in the 'George Washington Carver Week' celebration, held last week. The choir was featured on Television Station WQED Monday night. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Schenley High School choir performing in WQED television station studio during George Washington Carver Week program
